'''Josué Casimir''' (born 24 September 2001) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right-back]], [[right wing-back]] or [[striker (association football)|striker]] for French {{French football updater|Auxerre}} club [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]]. Born in Guadeloupe, he represents the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Club career==
Casimir made his professional debut with Le Havre in a 1–0 [[Ligue 2]] win over [[USL Dunkerque]] on 24 October 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2020/10/24/france/ligue-2/usl-dunkerque/le-havre-athletic-club-football-associat/3287888/|title=Dunkerque vs. Le Havre - 24 October 2020|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

On 6 June 2025, Casimir signed a three-season contract with [[AJ Auxerre|Auxerre]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=AJ Auxerre|url=https://www.aja.fr/josue-casimir-premiere-recrue-de-laja/|title=Josué Casimir première recrue de l'AJA|trans-title=Josué Casimir, AJA's first recruit|date=6 June 2025|access-date=30 July 2025|language=fr}}</ref>

==International career==
Casimir was born in the French overseas territory Guadeloupe to Haitian parents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haititempo.com/foot-un-jeune-attaquant-dorigine-haitienne-suivit-par-le-milan-ac/|title=Foot: Un jeune attaquant d'origine haïtienne suivit par le Milan AC ! - Haiti-Tempo|date=7 May 2021}}</ref> He holds French and Haitian descent.<ref>{{Cite web |last=JEROME |first=Joly |date=9 June 2020 |title=Foot-Interview: Josué CASIMIR privilége l'équipe de France en premier lieu. |url=http://total-sport.fr/index.php/2020/06/08/foot-interview-josue-casimir-privilege-lequipe-de-france-en-premier-lieu/}}</ref> He played for the [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe U20]]s at the [[2020 CONCACAF U-20 Championship qualifying]] matches, with three goals in three games.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.concacaf.com/en/under-20s-men/article/guadeloupe-and-curacao-stay-unbeaten-in-cu20-qualifying|title=Guadeloupe and Curacao stay unbeaten in CU20 Qualifying|website=www.concacaf.com}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]] for a set of [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches in October 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haitisportuniversel.com/2025/10/02/eliminatoires-mondial-2026-josue-casimir-un-renfort-de-choix-pour-les-grenadiers/|title=Éliminatoires Mondial 2026 : Josué Casimir, un renfort de choix pour les Grenadiers !|first=Jean Fritzner|last=Bysson|date=2 October 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Casimir is the younger brother of the Guadeloupean international footballer Stevenson Casimir.<ref>{{Cite web|date=15 February 2020|title=Des instants " magiques " pour les frères Casimir|url=https://liguefoot-guadeloupe.fff.fr/simple/des-instants-magiques-pour-les-freres-casimir/|access-date=16 May 2021|website=[[Guadeloupean League of Football|Ligue guadeloupéenne de football]]|language=fr}}</ref>

